properties.abstract: If you start from Pointe de la Plaine Morte, you reach Rohrbachstein pretty fast. Those who want to take it easier, can enjoy an original summit in a terrific high alpine landscape characterised by the Glacier de la Plaine Morte and the surrounding summits. There are turquoise or deeply blue mountain lakes glowing deep below, and on the descent to Iffigenalp the vast landscape of Rawilpass does not fail to impress the hikers.
properties.subtitle: A rock castle on a mountain of rubble
properties.title: From Wisshorelücke and on the west face

sac_photos.title: Scrambling on the summit structures of Rohrbachstein
The unique structure of the Rohrbachstein summit with an attractive route and an excellent view

segments.description: From the aerial cable way station Glacier-de-la-Plaine-Morte take the marked mountain hiking trail towards Wildstrubelhütte across Pointe de la Plaine Morte, then descend northward past Pointe de Vatseret and ascend to Wisshorelücke (2851 m). Continue south-westward until the mountain hiking trail descends southward through a steep chimney.
segments.title: Glacier-de-la-Plaine-Morte – Bifurcation of the mountain hiking trail (chimmney)

segments.description:
Still above the chimney branch off the trail and ascend to Rohrbachstein more or less on the border between Berne and Valais. At first you hike on slabs and scree, further up it is fine rubble with faint trails and cairns. Go north round the summit rocks until you end on the western face. Now, helped by fixed ropes, scramble up to the summit on rocky steps, through corners and over ledges. 
On the same itinerary hike back to the chimney where you find again the mountain hiking trail.

photos.caption: Scrambling on the summit structures of Rohrbachstein
Like a patchwork quilt the colourful walls of rubble extend towards Wetzsteihore. Wildhorn is in the background.

segments.title: Bifurcation of the mountain hiking trail (chimney) – Rohrbachstein –back to the bifurcation

segments.description: From the chimney go back to Wisshorelücke on the mountain hiking trail and descend, again on a mountain hiking trail, to Wildstrubelhütte.
segments.title: Bifurcation of the mountain hiking trail (chimney) – Wildstrubelhütte

segments.description: From Wildstrubelhütte towards Rawilpass. Branch off to the right (north) at the bifurcation on P. 2554 above Rawilseeleni, pass the lakes and descend to Iffigenalp via Blattihütte. On the lower part of the trail there are some rather exposed passages.
segments.title: Wildstrubelhütte SAC – Iffigenalp

segments.description: From Rohrbachstein descend on the Valais side: from the summit go back to the aforementioned chimney. Descend through the chimney (fixed rope, iron steps) and continue down past Weisshornsee (Lac de Huiton), at the bifurcation P. 2448 branch off eastward, cross Col de l’Arpochey and hike down to the Cabane-des-Violettes gondola station. Chimney–Cabane-des-Violettes T3, 2 h 30 min.
segments.title: Variant: Bifurcation of the mountain hiking trail (chimney) – Cabane-des-Violettes CAS

segments.description: From Barrage du Rawil / Lac de Tseuzier (bus from Sion): attractive ascent above the artificial lake and across the vast Rawilpass. The mountain hiking trails are marked. Barrage – Rohrbachstein ca. 5 h. The same route can be undertaken on the descent, too. Unfortunately, there are few bus connections from/to Barrage du Rawil.
segments.title: Variant: Barrage du Rawil – Rohrbachstein
